==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oncost
<hw>On"cost`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Accounting)</fld> <def>In cost
accounting, expenditure which is involved in the process of manufacture
or the performance of work and which cannot be charged directly to any
particular article manufactured or work done (as where different kinds
of goods are produced), but must be allocated so that each kind of goods
or work shall bear its proper share.</def> <mark>[Brit.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>oncotomy</ent>⟦br⟧
